description: Superman must defeat the Japanese Sandman when he traps the shipping magnate and Jimmy Olsen.
name: The Japanese Sandman Pt. 2

description: Krypto encounters an alien spy who creates disasters on Earth as part of an invasion attempt.
name: The Spy From Outer Space Part 1

description: Superboy must be rescued by Krypto when he follows the spy to his home planet and the system's red sun drains his powers.
name: The Spy From Outer Space Part 2

description: A criminal scientist has created a sonic beam transmitter with which he can cause Krypto to turn belligerent.
name: Krypto's Calamitous Capers

description: A man pretending to be from Krypton sets a trap for Superboy by promising the ability to inject immunity from kryptonite.
name: The Man Who Knew Superboy's Secret

description: A dragon whose egg is mistakenly taken by deep sea divers becomes violent until Superboy sets things right - but the egg is later stolen by undersea pirates.
name: The Deep Sea Dragon

description: A sickly billionaire vows to give away his fortune to charity if he can be made to laugh.
name: Super Clown of Smallville

description: When Superboy drills to the Earth's core, he finds a glowing black sphere that draws out a crystalloid being.
name: The Visitor from the Earth's Core

description: A scientist's growth serum makes a pygmy elephant into a giant beast; the scientist developed an antidote but his bitterly jealous assistant sabotages the experiment.
name: The Beast that went Berzerk

description: Two alien children cause havoc on Earth through their innocent play.
name: Superboy's Strangest Foe

description: An undersea volcano releases an impish water being who causes havoc on solid ground.
name: The Capricious Crony

description: When a Kryptonian space probe is found, it contains weapons, one of which accidentally blinds Superboy.
name: Krypto, Super Seeing-Eye Dog

description: Clark Kent's young friend Timmy finds a magician's mantle that transports him back in time to the jousting fields of Camelot and King Arthur.
name: The Black Knight

description: Superboy must convince three alien warriors that Earth is populated by metahumans.
name: Operation Counter Invasion

description: Superboy must help a circus being sabotaged by the ringmaster's former partner.
name: The Jinxed Circus

description: Superboy must work to stop a violent hurricane.
name: Hurricane Fighters

description: A scientist tests a kryptonite antidote on Superboy that does not work, but which he accidentally mixed with plant growth serum that causes big problems.
name: Superboy's Super-Dilemma

description: Spotting two criminals during a costume ball, Clark Kent decides to use his devil costume to masquerade as the real devil
name: A Devil of a Time

description: Robotville is an experimental city controlled by machine beings, which suddenly go on a rampage at the programming of the city's evil main engineer.
name: The Revolt of Robotville

description: A saurian beast rampages through a Central American village before suddenly going docile, and the reason why is exploited by a gang of thieves.
name: The Beast With Two Faces

description: During a school exploration of a canyon, Clark Kent and Lana Lang are captured by fugitive gangster "Ape" Hanson and his mob.
name: The Gorilla Gang

description: In the jungle of Africa a mysterious mist transmutes an albino creature into any form.
name: The Chameleon Creature

description: Superboy must help a crew of interplanetary authorities ) pursue an evil scientist whose weaponry is causing disasters on Earth.
name: The Great Space Race

description: A scientist is irradiated by the energy of a rogue star, turning him into an evil being with super energy emanating from his hands.
name: Finger of Doom

description: Dog thieves are on the rampage until Krypto, posing as an innocent dog, is captured.
name: Krypto, K-9 Detective

description: Four fugitives encounter an iceberg in which a caveman has been frozen in suspension and now is revived.
name: The Neanderthal Caveman Caper

description: Three school bullies are taught a needed lesson from Superboy.
name: The Terrible Trio

description: Breaking up a meteor shower, Superboy and Krypto are struck by a kryptonite meteor, which gives Krypto amnesia.
name: Forget Me Not, Superdog

description: An alien youth has created superpowers implanted in a blue costume and begins showing off on Earth.
name: Superboy Meets Mighty Lad

description: After destroying a fireball that bombards Earth, Superboy is hailed as a king by an alien civilization whose populace is held hostage by Chrystal people, the source of the fireball.
name: King Superboy

description: Space authorities recruit Superboy to help them track down a gang of pirates.
name: Double Trouble, Double Doom

description: Alien beings capture astronauts and drain their energy into their warriors, and proceed to do the same to Superboy.
name: The Trap of the Super Spacemen

description: Three vicious prospectors attack a pair of aliens who seek only sanctuary in a mountain countryside.
name: The Space Refugees

description: A Universal Molecule is used in an experiment that goes wrong; a scientist is irradiated and Superboy must fly 1,000 years into the future, where the Molecule will have grown to large size.
name: The Monster Molecule

description: A gang hopes to use a kryptonite amulet against Superboy, but in trying to lure him into their trap they accidentally detonate an underground oilfield - which causes them to lose the amulet, which is later found by Lana Lang.
name: The Great Kryptonite Caper

description: A dragon who can freeze anything battles Aquaman.
name: The Ice Dragon

description: Mole men use drilling submarines to attack Atlantis.
name: The Deadly Drillers

description: An evil sea queen attacks Atlantis with robot bull whales.
name: Vassa, Queen Of The Mermen

description: Aquaman has invented a ray that enlarges plankton, but the device is stolen by Black Manta .
name: The Microscopic Monsters

description: An advanced race of eight-armed beings capture Aquaman.
name: The Onslaught Of The Octomen

description: Alien fish beings from Saturn attack the Earth.
name: The Satanic Saturnians

description: The Brain, a mutant scientist, uses his intelligence to combat Aquaman.
name: "The Brain, The Brave And The Bold" - The Brain, a mutant scientist, uses his intelligence to combat Aquaman.

description: A satantic marauder and his men attack an oxygen exchange plant before attacking Atlantis.
name: Mephisto's Marine Marauders

description: A mermaid society is attacked by a mastodon-like sea giant.
name: Goliaths Of The Deep-Sea Gorge

description: A raider with a powerful animator beam turns a boulder of poisonous phosphorus into a sea giant.
name: The Sinister Sea Scamp

description: Aquaman helps the Navy test an undersea fightercraft, a ship that is captured by Black Manta
name: The Devil Fish

description: A gang of pirates wield a giant submarine robot.
name: The Sea Scavengers

description: The Brain receives a being molded into a perfect double of Aquaman from Reflecto of the Planet Imago in a plot to take over Atlantis.
name: The Mirror-Man From Planet Imago

description: Aquaman must deal with an evil warlock.
name: The Sea Sorcerer

description: A sky pirate battles the Aqua team.
name: The Sea-Snares Of Captain Sly

description: Mera unwittingly opens an artificial seahorse that launches an attack on Atlantis
name: The Undersea Trojan Horse

description: Vassa commands a fleet of laser-drill ships for another attack on Atlantis.
name: The Vicious Villainy Of Vassa

description: The Brain uses a powerful computer that calculates the formula for a ray that will make sea beings float helplessly to the ocean surface, until Aquaman recruits the help of a cyclopsian fish to stop him
name: Programmed For Destruction

description: NASA launches the Aqua team to explore an all-ocean planet called Q-344. While there, they discover that two races, the fish-like Quatix and the Bimphars, are at war.
name: The War Of The Quatix And The Bimphars

description: A mischievous sea genie grants three wishes to Aqualad that cause havoc.
name: Three Wishes To Trouble

description: A large metallic ball that opens the ocean floor and creates lavish growth becomes the source of conflict between two races, the Tortoids and the Lizard People.
name: The Silver Sphere

description: Alien insects land outside a nuclear plant to destroy the station.
name: Invasion of the Beetle-Men

description: A criminal scientist gives life to plants for malevolent purposes
name: The Plant Master

description: A scientist teams with an alien warlord.
name: The House of Doom

description: A radiation experiment gone wrong creates a powerful creature out of an ordinary ant.
name: The Chemo-Creature

description: A criminal scientist unleashes a powerful robot to battle The Flash and Kid Flash.
name: Take a Giant Step

description: Blue Bolt, an alien being with the same superspeed as The Flash, attacks the Earth.
name: To Catch a Blue Bolt

description: The Guardians of the Universe summon Green Lantern to battle Evil Star a criminal with superpowers identical to Green Lantern's.
A space fugitive captures Kairo to divert Green Lantern from a breakout of prisoners on a penal planet.
name: The Vanishing World

description: An alien queen attacks the planet Oa.
name: Sirena, Empress of Evil

description: Hawkman must fly to Pluto to defeat an interplanetary brigand whose laser ray is decimating Earth
name: Peril from Pluto

description: Octo-armed aliens capture a manned space probe and use it to lure Hawkman to a trap.
name: A Visit to Venus

description: Malevolent pranksters from Jupiter use teleportation rays on Hawkman and their jailers.
name: The Twenty Third Dimension

description: After being urged by her team, Emily (Vanessa Hudgens) sets her sights on the dating world but unknowingly falls for one of the Riddler's henchmen (guest-star Robert Buckley). Meanwhile, Teddy (Danny Pudi) and Ron (Ron Funches) find a Batman artifact and discover Van's (Alan Tudyk) superhero fantasy.
name: Emily Dates A Henchman

description: With Jason's funeral around the corner, the Blossom family moves forward with last minute preparations -- and a secret agenda. Meanwhile, Archie's (KJ Apa) attempt to refocus his energy on football comes to a halt when an opportunity to work with a new music mentor presents itself. Betty (Lili Reinhart) dives deeper into her investigation of Jason's death and unearths some dark revelations about her family. Elsewhere, after uncovering secrets about her own family, Veronica (Camila Mendes) forms an unlikely friendship with Cheryl (Madelaine Petsch), who is having a tougher time with Jason's impending funeral than she lets on. Finally, Hermoine (Marisol Nichols) turns to Fred (Luke Perry) for help after receiving a cryptic message from the Southside Serpents.
name: Heart of Darkness

description: "Between Two Armies" - The warring factions of the Rock People and the Crystal People from Mercury use Earth as a base for their conflict. The Justice League must bring peace to the warring factions before Earth ends up in the crossfire.
name: Between Two Armies

description: A criminal warlord named Rom-Nex uses a gravity device to attack Earth. The Justice League are warned in time by a rebel named Val-Kar.
name: Target Earth

description: A malevolent warlord named Mastermind lures the Justice League to a trap on a mammoth desert mesa so that they will not interfere in his plans to take over Earth.
name: Bad Day on Black Mountain

description: An unmanned spaceship unleashes multi-armed robots to attack Earth.
name: The Monster Machine

description: Alien hunters must jettison vicious creatures else their damaged craft will crash, and the Titans must find the now-rampaging beasts.
name: The Space Beast Round-Up

description: A scientist and his son must be rescued from an alien tribe high in the mountains.
name: Operation: Rescue

description: Batman and Robin are thrown for a loop when they arrest Joker and Penguin for crimes they didn't commit.
name: My Crime Is Your Crime

description: Mr. Freeze causes havoc in his quest to ransom $1 billion from the city and he uses a captured whale for his caper.
name: The Cool, Cruel Mr. Freeze

description: Joker raids technology firms to build a powerful solar mirror he can use as a laser weapon.
name: How Many Herring in a Wheelbarrow

description: Catwoman traps Batman and exposes him to a radioactive gas that will allow her to identify him in his secret identity.
name: The Nine Lives of Batman

description: Bruce Wayne is captured by Penguin in the robbery of a valuable ruby. Unfortunately for Penguin, Catwoman is also after the ruby.
name: Bubi, Bubi, Who's Got the Ruby

description: Riddler and Penguin try to expose Batman by staging a mammoth birthday party for him and wealthy businessman Bruce Wayne.
name: The Big Birthday Caper

description: A deadly contest is staged by Joker, Penguin, and Riddler to one up each other and gain control of Gotham City's criminal empire. Soon Catwoman gets involved.
name: Partners in Peril

description: Joker runs for Gotham mayor and is able to win.
name: Hizzoner the Joker

description: Penguin seizes a mammoth computer to use to outwit Batman and Robin.
name: The Crime Computer

description: Catwoman steals the Crown Jewels, which Joker is also after.
name: A Game of Cat and Mouse

description: A youth who bears a stunning resemblance to Robin is used by Catwoman when he ends up with amnesia.
name: Will the Real Robin Please Stand Up

description: A flamboyant criminal pastry chef named Simon the Pieman and his gang steal valuables under the cover of the fairgrounds after they had disposed of Joker, Penguin, Riddler, Catwoman, and Mr. Freeze.
name: Simon the Pieman

deck: West infiltrates a paramilitary organization bent on overthrowing the U.S. government.
description:
When a senator's daughter's fiance tips her off that he's joined a paramilitary organization dedicated to overthrowing the U.S. government, West goes undercover in the organization.

Martin Landau guest stars as the leader of the group, General Grimm.
name: The Night of the Red-Eyed Madmen

description: Catwoman sends Batman a cat for Valentine's Day, a cat whose fur gives off radio waves.
name: From Catwoman with Love

description: Simon the Pieman steals four million Turkish coins and is pursued to an electrical plant.
name: A Perfidious Pieman Is Simon

description: A freak bombardment of meteors made of pure ice allows Mr. Freeze to stage a mammoth hoax.
name: The Fiendishly Frigid Fraud

description: Riddler plans to blow up Gotham's art gallery and winds up trapping The Caped Crusaders as well.
name: The Jigsaw Jeopardy

description: Joker, Penguin, and Riddler are after an Incan Treasure Map. They plan to break up the Dynamic Duo by making Robin jealous of Batgirl.
name: It Takes Two to Make a Team

description: Penguin unexpectedly goes straight.
name: A Bird Out of Hand

description: Robin seems to lose his skills after he rescues a man from drowning thanks to the Joker.
name: The Joke's on Robin

description: Penguin commits crimes and frames them on Batman even though he's supposedly incarcerated.
name: In Again, Out Again Penguin

description: Joker makes a movie about pirates - cover to find the haul from a long-forgotten armored car theft.
name: Long John Joker

description: Riddler becomes an expert at disguises.
name: 1001 Faces of the Riddler

description: Real penguins wind up helping Penguin and Joker.
name: Two Penguins Too Many
